# JSON Response Conventions

Every route handler must respond with JSON. No plain text, no HTML.

## Status Codes

```js
// ❌ BAD
res.send('OK')
res.status(200).json({ ... })  // wrong status for POST creation
res.status(500).json({ ... })  // never return 500 manually

// ✅ GOOD — validation failure
res.status(400).json({ error: "name, email and message are required" })

// ✅ GOOD — POST success
res.status(201).json({ success: true, data: { name, email, message } })

// ✅ GOOD — auth failure
res.status(401).json({ error: "Unauthorized" })
```

## Body Destructuring

Always guard against missing body:

```js
const { name, email, message } = req.body || {}
```
